[% META
        title = "Documentation System Audit & Planning"
   description = "Comprehensive audit and planning for Comserv documentation system - documentation files, code compatibility, and system improvements"
   roles = "admin,developer"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "system"
   page_version = "0.05"
   last_updated = "Thu Dec 18 2025"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/DOCUMENTATION_SYSTEM_AUDIT_PLAN.tt,v 0.05 2025/12/18 shanta Exp shanta - Added documentation_role_access.tt to Phase 1 (item 14); Added Code-to-Documentation Compliance Issues section with findings on role hierarchy, debug code, and format violations; Added links and file paths to audit table' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;">Documentation System Audit & Planning</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;">
        Last Updated: 2025-12-18 | 
        Version: 0.05 |
        Author: Shanta | 
        Status: In Progress - Phase 1 Audit with Code Compliance Findings
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;">Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.8;">
                This document serves as the master audit and planning guide for the Comserv documentation system. It systematically inventories all documentation files, compares documentation against code implementations, and identifies areas for improvement. We are building this audit incrementally, one documentation file at a time.
            </p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.8;">
                <strong>Methodology:</strong> For each documentation file, we will:
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 2em;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">Ask clarifying questions about the file's purpose and completeness</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">Create a properly formatted .tt file with complete META tags</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">Compare documentation content to actual code implementation</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">Identify any gaps, inconsistencies, or improvements needed</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">Log findings to this plan for future cleanup work</li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;" id="toc">Table of Contents</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 2em;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#audit-summary">Audit Summary</a></li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#phase-1">Phase 1: Documentation System Documentation Files</a></li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#phase-2">Phase 2: Code Controller Audit</a></li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#phase-3">Phase 3: Consolidation & Cleanup</a></li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#findings">Key Findings</a></li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#improvement-plan">Improvement Plan</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;" id="audit-summary">Audit Summary</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <strong>Current Status:</strong> Phase 1 - Initiating documentation system files audit
            </p>
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; line-height: 1.8;">
                <tr style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg);">
                    <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Item</th>
                    <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Description</th>
                    <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Status</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Total Documentation Files Found</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Approximately 300+ .tt files in Documentation folder</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--success-color);">✓ Identified</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Documentation System Files</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Files describing how the documentation system works</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--warning-color);">⧖ Starting</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Code Controllers Audit</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Compare documentation files to actual code</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-muted-color);">⧐ Pending</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Consolidation Work</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Merge duplicate/related documentation</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-muted-color);">⧐ Pending</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;" id="phase-1">Phase 1: Documentation System Documentation Files</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                Audit files that describe how the documentation system itself works (for both developers and documentation creators).
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;">Audit Progress</h3>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--primary-color); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">Audit Compliance Definition</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.8;">
                    <strong>Compliant</strong> means: Document accurately reflects how the system currently works AND matches planned behavior. Code violations or future improvements are noted separately but do not block compliance status.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--info-color); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">Documentation Template Files Identified</h4>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 1.5em;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>documentation_tt_template.tt</strong>
                        <ul style="margin-left: 1.5em; margin-top: var(--spacing-small); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Status:</strong> ✓ Reviewed & Complete</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Current State:</strong> Well-structured, uses proper META tags with return-to-menu button in footer</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Issue Found:</strong> None</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Maintain current implementation</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Action Needed:</strong> None</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>documentation_system.tt</strong>
                        <ul style="margin-left: 1.5em; margin-top: var(--spacing-small); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Status:</strong> ⧖ To Review</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Current State:</strong> File exists but appears to be Markdown content in .tt file (not proper format)</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Issue Found:</strong> Missing META block, no proper TT structure</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Reformat to proper .tt with META tags</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Action Needed:</strong> Ask clarifying questions before reformatting</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>documentation_workflow.tt</strong>
                        <ul style="margin-left: 1.5em; margin-top: var(--spacing-small); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Status:</strong> ⧖ To Review</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Current State:</strong> File exists with proper structure but may be outdated</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Issue Found:</strong> Missing META block</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Recommendation:</strong> Add META block and verify content matches current workflow</li>
                            <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Action Needed:</strong> Ask clarifying questions about current workflow</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--warning-color); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">Documentation Organization Files</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.8;">
                    These files help organize and categorize the documentation system:
                </p>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 1.5em;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>documentation_config.json</strong> - Configuration file for documentation categories</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>admin_guides.tt / admin_guides_template.tt</strong> - Template for admin documentation</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>developer_guides.tt</strong> - Template for developer documentation</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>user_guides.tt</strong> - Documentation for regular users</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;">Audit Criteria for Each File</h3>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.8;">
                    Each file is evaluated against FOUR comprehensive criteria. The "Purpose" column accumulates detailed audit findings as we review each file.
                </p>
                <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 2em;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Template Compliance:</strong> Does file match documentation_tt_template.tt structure? (META block, PageVersion, TOC, sections, CSS variables, footer)</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Code Accuracy:</strong> Does documentation match the actual code it describes? Check against source controllers, models, and utilities.</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>System Plan Alignment:</strong> Does file serve documented purpose in the documentation system? Does it align with Phase 1, 2, 3 goals?</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Consolidation Opportunities:</strong> Are there duplicate files, overlapping content, or files that should merge?</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;">Phase 1: Complete Inventory List</h3>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <h4 style="color: var(--info-color); margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">Documentation System Files to Review (14 Files)</h4>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.8;">
                    These files describe how the documentation system works. We will review each one to verify its purpose, check for proper formatting (META tags, .tt structure), identify duplication, and determine if updates are needed.
                </p>
            </div>

            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.9em;">
                <tr style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg);">
                    <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: left;">File Name</th>
                    <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: left;">File Type</th>
                    <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: left;">Purpose</th>
                    <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">Status</th>
                    <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">Priority</th>
                </tr>

                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><a href="/Documentation/documentation_tt_template" style="color: var(--link-color);">Documentation/documentation_tt_template.tt</a></td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Template</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Standard template for all .tt documentation files (META block, TOC, sections, styling)</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--success-color); text-align: center;">✓ Complete</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">HIGH</td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><a href="/Documentation/documentation_system" style="color: var(--link-color);">Documentation/documentation_system.tt</a></td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">.tt File</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>AUDIT FINDINGS:</strong> Template Compliance: ✓ PASS (proper META, PageVersion, TOC, CSS vars, footer). Code Accuracy: ❌ CRITICAL GAPS - (1) Docs claim "higher roles see lower role docs" (line 67) but NO role hierarchy implemented (code only does direct matching - Documentation.pm:437-459). (2) Docs claim role-based filtering works but TEMPORARY DEBUG CODE (Documentation.pm:414-416) bypasses ALL filtering showing all pages to all users (marked "REMOVE THIS LATER"). (3) Docs undocument hardcoded usernames (Shanta, admin) getting special CSC access (Documentation.pm:636-643). System Plan: ⚠ File describes intended behavior but code doesn't match. Consolidation: ✓ No duplicates. Status: Template-compliant but content has 3 code-accuracy mismatches.</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--warning-color); text-align: center;">⚠ Code-Gaps</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">HIGH</td>
                </tr>

                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><a href="/Documentation/Documentation" style="color: var(--link-color);">Documentation/Documentation.md</a></td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">TT (hybrid)</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>AUDIT FINDINGS:</strong> Purpose: Landing/index page displaying docs based on user role/site (NOT system documentation). Template: ❌ FAIL - Minimal META (only title), no PageVersion, no debug conditional, no TOC, no proper .tt structure (has inline CSS, Template Toolkit conditionals but not template standard). Code Accuracy: ✓ PASS - Correctly implements dynamic documentation listing (cards, role-based filtering, admin actions). System Plan: ✓ Serves intended purpose as display layer. Format Issue: File is .md extension but contains Template Toolkit code (hybrid). Consolidation: ⚠ Related to but separate from documentation_system.tt (which explains HOW the system works; this DISPLAYS results). Status: Functionally correct but violates format standards - should be .tt file with proper META block.</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--warning-color); text-align: center;">⚠ Format</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">HIGH</td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><a href="/Documentation/documentation_workflow" style="color: var(--link-color);">Documentation/documentation_workflow.tt</a></td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">.tt File</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>AUDIT FINDINGS:</strong> Purpose: HOW TO WRITE documentation (workflow guide for editors/developers). Template: ❌ FAIL - Missing META block entirely, has PageVersion (v1.0 2024/05/31 - outdated 7mo). No title/author/status in META. Uses non-standard structure (class="documentation-page" not container grid). No CSS variables for theming. Code Accuracy: ✓ PASS - Workflow steps appear valid. System Plan: ✓ Purpose aligns with plans. Currency: ⚠ Outdated (May 2024, last updated Dec 18 needed). Consolidation: ⚠ Similar content to Documentation_Workflow.tt (capitalized version). Status: Needs META block, update timestamp, and consolidation check against Documentation_Workflow.tt.</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--warning-color); text-align: center;">⚠ META Fix</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">HIGH</td>
                </tr>

                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><a href="/Documentation/Documentation_Workflow" style="color: var(--link-color);">Documentation/Documentation_Workflow.tt</a></td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">.tt File</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>AUDIT FINDINGS:</strong> Purpose: Documentation workflow guide (alternate version to documentation_workflow.tt). Template: ❌ FAIL - No META block, only PageVersion (v1.00 2024/08/09 - outdated 4+mo). Has minimal header (title, author, status in text, not META). Malformed structure (h1-h2 tags, pre block, but inconsistent TT conditionals lines 54-55). No CSS variables. Code Accuracy: ⚠ PARTIAL - Directory structure shown may not match current state (references sites/mcoop which may be site-specific). System Plan: ⚠ Incomplete - file appears truncated/broken (lines 32-53 are mostly blank, lines 54+ show debug code fragment). Consolidation: ❌ CRITICAL DUPLICATE - Nearly identical purpose to documentation_workflow.tt (lowercase version). Status: Malformed file, outdated, incomplete content, duplicate content. RECOMMENDATION: DELETE or consolidate with documentation_workflow.tt.</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--error-color); text-align: center;">❌ Broken</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">HIGH</td>
                </tr>

                <tr>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><a href="/Documentation/documentation_config" style="color: var(--link-color);">Documentation/config/documentation_config.json</a></td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Config (JSON)</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>AUDIT FINDINGS:</strong> Purpose: Master config for documentation categories (6380 lines, 15+ categories, role/site filtering). Template: N/A - JSON config. Code Accuracy: ✓ PASS - Matches controller code usage (Documentation.pm loads via _load_categories_from_config()). Categories include: ai-agents, tutorials, controllers, modules, environment, operations, ui_features, etc. Role/site filtering configured correctly. System Plan: ✓ Aligns with documented category structure. Completeness: ⚠ NEEDS DOCUMENTATION - File has no inline comments explaining purpose, structure, or how to add categories. Consolidation: ✓ No duplicates (unique config file). Status: Functional but undocumented. RECOMMENDATION: Create documentation_config_guide.tt if not already done.</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--success-color); text-align: center;">✓ Complete</td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">HIGH</td>
                </tr>

                <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><a href="/Documentation/documentation_config_guide" style="color: var(--link-color);">Documentation/documentation_config_guide.tt</a></td>
                    <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">.tt File</td>
