            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); margin-top: var(--spacing-large); line-height: 1.6;">Review Process</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                For each file in the above list, we will:
            </p>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 2em;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Verify File Purpose</strong> - Confirm what the file documents and check if it's actually documentation about the system</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Check Format</strong> - Verify proper .tt structure with META block, or identify if it should be .tt instead of .md</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Identify Duplication</strong> - Check if multiple files document the same topic (e.g., documentation_system.tt vs documentation_system_overview.tt)</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Verify Currency</strong> - Check if content matches current system implementation</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Plan Action</strong> - Determine if file needs reformatting, consolidation, updating, or archival</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Log Findings</strong> - Record all decisions in the Phase 1 results section below</li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); margin-top: var(--spacing-large); line-height: 1.6;">Next Step: Begin File Reviews</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                We will now proceed through the list, starting with <strong>Priority HIGH</strong> files (items 1-7), one at a time. Each file review will identify its true purpose, current state, and required actions. Consolidation opportunities will be identified during this process.
            </p>
        </div>
