    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;" id="findings">Key Findings (Preliminary)</h2>
            
            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--success-color); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">Strengths</h3>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 1.5em;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">✓ Comprehensive template system with proper CSS variable support</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">✓ Good separation of concerns (controllers, scanning, config)</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">✓ Well-organized directory structure with categories</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">✓ META block usage for metadata extraction</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">✓ Support for both .tt and .md file formats</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--warning-color); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">Issues Identified</h3>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 1.5em;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">⚠ Some documentation files using Markdown format inside .tt files (improper structure)</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">⚠ Some documentation system files missing proper META blocks</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">⚠ Multiple documentation files describing similar features (potential duplication)</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">⚠ Documentation workflow may be outdated (need verification)</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">⚠ <strong>CRITICAL: Code-to-Documentation Mismatches Found</strong> - See detailed compliance section below</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--error-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--error-color); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">⚠ Code-to-Documentation Compliance Issues (Audit Finding)</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                    During initial Phase 1 audit, code compliance analysis revealed <strong>4 critical discrepancies</strong> between documentation claims and actual implementation:
                </p>
                
                <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.85em;">
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg);">
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: left;">Issue</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: left;">File</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: left;">What Docs Claim</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: left;">Code Reality</th>
                        <th style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color); text-align: center;">Priority</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>1. Role Hierarchy Not Implemented</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">documentation_system.tt (Lines 67)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">"Higher roles can see documentation for lower roles"</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">No role hierarchy exists; only direct role matching with no "level" concept (Documentation.pm:437-459)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--error-color); text-align: center;">CRITICAL</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>2. Visibility Rules Disabled (Debug Code)</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Documentation.pm (Lines 414-416)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">"Visibility rules apply" - "Users can only see documentation for their site/role"</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">TEMPORARY DEBUG CODE bypasses ALL filtering: shows ALL pages to ALL users regardless of role or site (marked "REMOVE THIS LATER")</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--error-color); text-align: center;">CRITICAL</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr style="background-color: var(--secondary-color);">
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>3. Hardcoded Username Access</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Documentation.pm (Lines 378-387)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">"Role-based access control" - grants access by role</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Hardcoded usernames ('Shanta', 'admin') get admin role for CSC site only - undermines documented role-based system</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--error-color); text-align: center;">HIGH</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>4. documentation_role_access.tt Format</strong></td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">documentation_role_access.tt</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">"Proper .tt documentation files" with META blocks</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Contains raw Markdown format (# headers, no META block, not proper .tt structure)</td>
                        <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--warning-color); text-align: center;">HIGH</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>

                <h4 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: var(--spacing-medium); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">Remediation Required</h4>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 1.5em;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Issue #1:</strong> Documentation must either document the absence of role hierarchy OR the code must implement role hierarchy as described</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Issue #2 (URGENT):</strong> Remove temporary debug code from Documentation.pm lines 414-416 before production deployment</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Issue #3:</strong> Replace hardcoded username checks with proper role-based logic or document this special case</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);"><strong>Issue #4:</strong> Convert documentation_role_access.tt to proper .tt format with META block and structured HTML</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-small) 0; margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                <h3 style="color: var(--info-color); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small); line-height: 1.6;">Areas for Investigation</h3>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8; margin-left: 1.5em;">
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">documentation_system.tt vs documentation_system.md - are both needed?</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">admin_guides.tt vs admin_guides_template.tt - separate purposes or duplicates?</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">How documentation_config.json relates to actual file discovery</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">Whether all controller files have corresponding documentation</li>
                    <li style="margin-bottom: var(--spacing-small);">Completeness of module documentation (Todo, Mail, ENCY, etc.)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.6;" id="improvement-plan">Improvement Plan</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); margin-bottom: var(--spacing-medium); line-height: 1.8;">
                Based on preliminary findings, here are improvements we will document and track:
            </p>
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0; line-height: 1.8;">
                <tr style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg);">
